tip.text: Scrambled eggs,charred beef and the walnut brown butter cake are a must. Cocktails are pretty good too. Kale and wild mushroom paella was too salty.

formattedAddress: 324 Lafayette St (btwn Bleecker & E Houston St)

tip.text: Amazing razor clams. Rabbit is served once a week (literally one rabbit a week), and we got lucky. But it was tough. The mushrooms, pearl onions, fava beans and arugula it sat on top of, was amazing.
Very poor service, at least for a Jean-Georges restaurant. Fish and chips was good.

formattedAddress: 18 E 16th St (btwn Union Sq W & 5th Ave)

tip.text: The Spanish omelette is good! And the mussels were really fresh.
The Serrano ham croquettes were so good we ordered them twice. Go for the rice with Iberian pork, chorizo and artichoke; and house salad isn't too bad too
Chef Chad is very knowledgeable and friendly. He remembers the details if you're a regular, and he makes you feel at home.
